SIMPLE: opianine
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: opianine
<hw>o"pi*a*nine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>An alkaloid (<chform>C22H23NO7</chform>) found in small quantity in
opium. It is identical with <altname>narcotine</altname>. It is present
in amounts up to 11% in <spn>Papaver somniferum</spn>, and is used
clinically as an antitussive.</def> <au>MI11</au>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> noscapine; narcosine; opian.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Opianyl</ent>⟦br⟧
